history.text: Hi Dunkirk seems like it is a good movie. I haven't seen it yet
Yes, I agree. I'm planing to see it this Saturday. Do you know whats it about ?
Work war two I think. It's directed by Christopher Nolan so it ought to be good.

Yes, I also like that it portrays the events from three different perspectives. Do you usually
 watch movies only based on their rating ?

Rotten Tomatoes rating? They usually have a good rating. Ratings in general I don't pay a lot of attention to. It says there is not much discussion or talking in the actual movie with more focus on the action and photography. That ought to be interesting.
Yes, do you think you would like a movie without much talking ? It says that the director focuses on creating suspense.

I think so because he is using music also so that will hold interest. And if the action is good and evacuation in war is sad but probably a good thing too if it means saving people so good photography and music would do it I think

I agree.  Also there is a wide variety of effects and the director used thousands of extras just to make everything believable
 and real.
yes. the actors ought to be good. I'm not familiar with the work of all of them but I think they'll work. the  filming started in Dunkirk so that ought to have a good background for the story.
Yes. the cast looks good and consists of actors that can really act. Also Tom Glynn-Carney stars who I really like.
Wow. it sounds like it has  a lot of action in it. Probably took a toll on the actors.
I feel that the story about the British solider (Tommy) is really exciting. He has a big heart and is always trying to help everybody
Yes, he sounds like the hero of the story. the review does say it doesn't have false herocis

Do you like movies that have a lot of suspens
e in them or do you prefer they go straight to the point ?
I like dramas and suspense is good. Not keen on war movies but if the photography and story work then yeah, they are good

I really like war films. Not that much interested in the story as long as the visuals are good and it's historically
 accurate.
Yes, we need to remember the stories as best we can without manufacturing them. it does sound like this one doesn't disappoint with the acttion
Did you like the story about Tommy, Alex and Gibson ?
Where they get saved? Yes, I haven't seen it yet but that does sound like a point that pulls the movie together.
It's also a really sad ending. But I think thats what you get from war in general. There is so much sadness, pain and destruction.
Yeah, that's the bad thing but it is war. Looks like they did a fire scene too with the oil slick that ignites.
The purpose of all that in my opinion is to warn this generation that war should be avoided at all costs.
If that would happen it would be a good thing. It says they had thousands of extras. Must of cost some money
I think I would really enjoy the scene where Bolton watches the last British soldier leave. It will be truly a heart warming scene
I read that and was thinking the same thing.And the evacuated 300,000.
Do you like movies with happy ending ?
Yeah of course. But I don't like real sappy ones. That's good they receive a hero's welcome. that ought to cheer up the movie a bit.
Yes, I think that people would feel happy when they leave the theaters.
Yep good conversation, see you soon !
